race.comment: Tricky. LUNA FIELD (13) races forward and got close second-up, caught late at Stawell, beaten 2.3L. He's improved and keeps the handy 3kg claim. Strips fitter and this is winnable. EXOTIC DANCER (12) is free running and posted a strong relative number at Clare (SA) before being swamped at Strathalbyn after crossing over from the 13 gate. Peaks today and will get it easier. Has a 2kg claim and her chance. MISS MAGOO (5) resumed at Kyneton and didn't have the best of it late. Has plenty up her sleeve and won her only second-up outing. Quick improvement is on the cards. JUDGE KELLIE (11) is speedy and from an inside barrier she can build on her win at Swan Hill.
